<br>
I'll start replies with Noonie.<br>
<br>
1.) When soloing those trans rods aren't super powerful no.  Mages can only get moderate regeneration at best and it isn't enough to make them &quot;ultra uber&quot; by any strench.  All you need is one cleric though, and they are ultra uber.  Besides, remember we didn't have any regen at all because we precast spells and use them more efficiently?  Would you rather go this root with everyone else or branch out into something more interesting?<br>
<br>
2.)  Necros and corpse summon and.. Well damage, I'm sorry, most of the high regen mobs, if not all are immune to disease, for good reason.  Lifetaps are notably unreliable on raids, and are very inefficient, and dots are great if... The mob lasts long enough, and other necros aren't around for stacking issues.  Again you have the problem of resistances as well.  Theres no lure DoTs after all.  As for pets, well why have a necro pet with a mage pet there.. And for that matter, why have a mage pet with a dire pet there?  Pets can become hard to control and often are excluded from raids.  Specially necro pets.  So even if they could summon one their spells are seen as more useful for cleric mana.  And right now it's understandable why.  I feel bad for necros, but thats another thread.<br>
<br>
3.)  Someone above stated that Verant was committing themselves to make raid downtime shorter.  Ok I can see that as good.  However it fell to us to replenish mana, and although the ability is neat, it's just something else that adds to our utility, and therefore raid power and usefulness, in a different direction from where we were going all this time anyway.  Its not just that though.<br>
<br>
Any time you have one ability that adds so much to a class I personally take a look and ask &quot;Is that really nessecery?&quot;  If it's something we began the class with then fine.  But mod rods were added later.  The first one isn't overpowered in the least.  The second though allows mages to chain nuke on any raid where a cleric isn't needed to his utmost.<br>
<br>
So my point was this one spell turns us from 3rd rate nuker +pet (which btw while we are nuking still does signifigant damage adding pet and DS's.)  to a mana powerhouse.  And we aren't bards, or enchanters, or even necromancers.<br>
<br>
What I'm thinking is this likely wasn't intended, and when Verant finds out they won't take it away from us, instead they will be lighter handed with other abilities that may actually point us in the direction we'd like to go.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sirellyn>Sirellyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#333333>(4/23/02 6:08:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=191.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Replies</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Trod IS powerfull on raids, does that mean that it should be nerfed? No imho. For god sake, mages have one really efficient way to contribute to raids don't nerf it. Why do magician always want to nerf all the things that are a little bit more powerfull that their average spells. Is it that magician are soo used to mediocres nukes on raids and very low ability to contribute ? CH, KEI, AE bard songs are also very powerfull. So nerf them too. All those that think that mod rod 2 is not powerfull just don't use them often or are in a guilde that only do mobs that they can kill easily. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
