1) Group lifetaps (great for AE mobs)<br>
2) Heal up to 800 hps in around 30 seconds with health transfers. (assuming you are fighting a mob you can lifetap)<br>
3) Mindwrack (Group mana tap for 300 mana each minute per person)<br>
4) FD pull (Yes, beleive it or not, necros make good pullers)<br>
5) Harmshield pull ( Necros have 2 invulnerabilty spells which can be very useful for pulling. You classes interested in AE encounters might find a necro more useful than you're standard tank type as you're puller)<br>
6) Dot damage (level 60 fire based dot funeral pyre is amazing. 2200 dmg in 54 seconds. That, in addition to our other dots, we can actually dish out quite a bit of damage. These days, pretty much every uber mob has at least one way for us to damage them. The majority have many more. It has pretty much become a situation of how much agro we can deal with from our dots verses what can we land on mobs now.)<br>
7) Back up crowd control ( in some cases, necros can actually play enchanter)<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Save you're ass once you die (Necros can rival rogues with their CR abilities. Beyone the obvious corpse summoning. Many necros have the pre nerf circlet of shadows which offers insta cast invis. With that item alone, we are able to utilize quite a few tricks aiding us in CR.<br>
9) Nuking (Necro lifetaps are fairly feeble but i suppose 720 damage lifetaps can add up. With the upgrade in Arch Lich, mana is rarely a problem. Add in those new focus items you mages supply us with and SPF, we do ok.)<br>
10) Group tap buffs ( Alot of mele seem to be quite happy with our Sta/str, ATK, and/or our AC taps)<br>
<br>
I'm sure there is more we can do that many people don't uderstand.<br>
<br>
Things we Can't do :<br>
<br>
1) Dunno...I keep proving myself wrong whenever i think of stuff like this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I know this was a bit off track from the initial topic of Mod Rod 2 being over powered. My opinion is it's great. Mod Rod 2 has shifted the mana regen focus away from necros allowing us to actually become useful on raids again.<br>
