Heh few things.<br>
<br>
First off, I don't know any class who loves just providing mana as their primary function in raids.  It's almost demeaning to consider your mana pool better used somewhere else.  My point before was that it was the only viable necro function in raids until mod rod 2 came around.  Which you argued, and I'll go over each point.<br>
<br>
1.)  Those group lifetaps do help, it's a pretty good secondary feature, but I keep hearing how hard it is to lifetap end boss encounters.  Am I wrong?  Most end boss mobs easy to lifetap?<br>
<br>
2.) Same as one.<br>
<br>
3.) More spells like that I've love to see.  So you don't have to keep casting, cast once and while it's working do other more useful things.  Even still sadly most spells from monsters are actually perfered over their melee abilities.  Special abilities like AoE's don't use mana anyway, so the draining point isn't too useful unless it's on those few mobs that actually complete heal.  Those are pretty rare end mobs.<br>
<br>
4.) FD pullers eh?  I really haven't seen too much of this, which of course doesn;t mean you guys aren't.  Harmshield would help with this I do suppose and it would be an option when no monk or SK is availible.<br>
<br>
5.) Same as 4.<br>
<br>
6.) Hmm ok. Funeral Pyre is an amazing DoT but I was told a pretty rare spell.  A bit more than even KEI.  And DoT stacking is great, but what if there are 2 necros there?  3? more?  The dots don't stack together, and that really hurts, making others rather redundant.  I'm also told you share one or two lines with shamen, so if they decide to dot too you are out of luck.  As for aggro, do you mean the case used to be what you could get to stick on the boss monsters, and now that much of it sticks casting too much will get you aggro?<br>
<br>
