<br>
10.) Those group tap buffs are a great place to head for the class.  I still feel you need more though.<br>
<br>
In most cases it seems like your best abilities are teriary at best.  You simply aren't really a damage dealing class in raids (which is fine, you don't want to have every class as one.)  You're versatility though is impressive, as wide or even better than druids.  But none of it is the best out of all the classes, that is you can sub at times for other classes, but in raids where those other classes are around you'd take a back seat.  Which is often the case unfortunatly.<br>
<br>
I guess I'm saying that most classes have a neiche in their roles at raids.  That is something they bring to almost every raid thats just as useful and no other class can do.  Up to now that seemed to be the mana pumping.. And now..<br>
